    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn vertical split diff mode with relativenumber set and one window maximized, the vertical split line partially disappears.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean --cmd 'set relativenumber'\r\n`10aa<CR><ESC>gg`\r\n:vnew\r\n`ab<CR><ESC>gg`\r\n:difft\r\n`<C-w><C-w>`\r\n:difft\r\n`<C-w>|j`\r\n\r\nVertical split line disappears.\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/12369962/9ed5d796-c64b-41c3-af71-f8816e253164)\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn nvim 0.9.5\r\nVertical split line doesn't disappear.\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/12369962/e29d1605-74d6-48d5-bd9a-ef11322ea2ea)\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.1-dev-53+g17fe405ad\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.52.0 using VTE 0.76.0 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
